<item>
            <title>[DERBY-2260] DatabaseMetaData.getTypeInfo() returns incorrect precision for VARCHAR FOR BIT DATA</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/DERBY-2260</link>
                <project id="10594" key="DERBY">Derby</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;PRECISION column for VARCHAR FOR BIT DATA is returned as 32762, but maximum precision is 32672 (6 &amp;amp; 7 swapped).&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;ij&amp;gt; create table z (a varchar(32672) for bit data);&lt;br/&gt;
0 rows inserted/updated/deleted&lt;br/&gt;
ij&amp;gt; create table z2(a varchar(32673) for bit data);&lt;br/&gt;
ERROR 42611: The length, precision, or scale attribute for column, or type mapping &apos;VARCHAR (32673) FOR BIT DATA&apos; is not valid.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
